          <ul class="warning-signs">
            <li><i class="fas fa-eye"></i> Visible water stains or discoloration</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-nose"></i> Musty or moldy odors</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-home"></i> Warped floors, walls, or ceilings</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-dollar-sign"></i> Unexplained water bill increases</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-thermometer-half"></i> Increased humidity levels indoors</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="content-block">
          <h3>Our Detailed {sub?.title || group.name} Restoration Process</h3>
          <p>Our certified technicians follow IICRC standards for {sub?.title || group.name.toLowerCase()} restoration. We begin with moisture mapping using thermal imaging to identify all affected areas, including hidden damage. Our industrial-grade equipment removes standing water and moisture from building materials, preventing secondary damage like mold growth.</p>
